## Robust and clustered standard errors

When observations are not independent, for example when the same subject contributes several
rows or when subjects are grouped into clusters, the model-based standard errors are too
small. The robust, or sandwich, variance corrects for this. Set `robust=True` for the
Lin-Wei sandwich estimator, and pass `cluster` to group correlated observations.

::: {#352a4c4e .cell execution_count=16}
``` {.python .cell-code}
# Load data and build the response
lung = gw.load_dataset("lung", backend="polars")
y = gw.Surv.right(lung["time"], event=(lung["status"] == 2))

# Fit with the Lin-Wei sandwich variance; coefficients are unchanged, SEs are adjusted
robust = gw.CoxPH().fit(y, lung[["age", "sex"]], robust=True)

# Show only the standard errors to compare against the model-based values
robust.to_frame(format="polars")[["term", "std_error"]]
```

